îíŸ@ee885b07fe86aadfb45aa0c51d554bf6f4c354f5e7128029a91972c688cb230b⁄Title: This week in Nushell #264
Path: Nushell
Content:
Ancient77 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13725] expanded multiple dots in path completions
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13848] allowed tab characters to be retained with 
``find``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13809] bumped rust version to 1.79.0
hustcer updated the release workflow: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13840] bumped the Nu version
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13800] added 
``aarch64-unknown-linux-musl``
 and 
``armv7-unknown-linux-musleabihf``
 targets
devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13838] fixed 
``try``
: Added 
``set_last_error()``
 to 
``prepare_error_handler()``
 for IR eval
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13796] fixed remaining mismatch for env handling in IR
ayax79 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13833] made 
``polars save``
 return an empty pipeline
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13829] migrated polars commands away from macros, removed custom DataFrame comparison
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13806] added documentation explanation explaining how to select all columns with 
``polars col``
nome 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13831] added a --number flag to 
``split column``
T3sT3ro 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13821] changed 
``clear``
 to clear scrollback by default
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13811] fixed IR for 
``try``
zhiburt 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13808] fixed a padding issue with header_on_border tables
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13801] changed ctrl-k to 
``cuttolineend``
 event in Config
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13763] fixed 
``path exists``
 on a non-directory file
Bahex 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13785] added a new 
``metadata access``
 command for debugging
